<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3343"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3343-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3343">How will Judge Sotomayor show fidelity to our Constitution?&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/5389-4049">tttahiti</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">5 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">By bestest buddy, Barack, sent me a personal e-mail to say, "I am proud to announce my nominee for the next Justice of the United States Supreme Court: Judge Sonia Sotomayor." ...yadda, yadda... and that she "would show fidelity to our Constitution."<br/><br/>It was a very nice letter and gave me the warm fuzzies.<br/><br/>My question is, "What Constitution? They threw that old rag away years ago.  I believe I heard that Dubbya used it for toilet paper. Save a tree, and all that.  Is there any chance of this Judge Sotomayor restoring it, or something vaguely reminicient?" It's a sentimental thing. I was never much for rules, but sometimes I like knowing that we have some, and what they are.<br/><br/>Hit the "thumbs-up" button if you would love to see a reply.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3343" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3343', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2294&topicID=3343')">Comments (1)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3343"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2294">Legal & Policy Challenges</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3343"></div>
